question:
For the following algorithm fragment, what is the basic operation count as a function of n?

for (i = 0; i < n; i++)
   a = a + i;

What is the time complexity of the following algorithm?

for (i = 0; i < n; i++)
   for (j = 0; j < n; j++)
        k = k + 1;

Given the algorithm below, what is its time complexity?

for (i = 1; i < n; i = i * 2)
   for (j = 0; j < i; j++)
        op(); // basic operation

Consider an algorithm with the following structure. What is its most precise time complexity class?

for (i = 0; i < n; i++)
   for (j = i; j < n; j++)
        for (k = j; k < n; k++)
            count++;
